# Biome Formatting Reference

This project uses Biome for linting and formatting (NOT ESLint/Prettier).

## Configuration Summary

From `biome.json`:

| Setting | Value |
|---------|-------|
| Indent style | Spaces |
| Indent width | 2 |
| Semicolons | Always |
| Trailing commas | All |
| JSX quotes | Double |
| Arrow parentheses | Always |
| Bracket spacing | True |

## Code Examples

### Semicolons: Always

```tsx
// ✅ Good
const value = 42;
export { Component };

// ❌ Bad
const value = 42
export { Component }
```

### Trailing Commas: All

```tsx
// ✅ Good
const config = {
  name: "usage-ui",
  version: "1.0.0",
};

const items = [
  "first",
  "second",
  "third",
];

// ❌ Bad
const config = {
  name: "usage-ui",
  version: "1.0.0"
};
```

### Arrow Parentheses: Always

```tsx
// ✅ Good
const double = (x) => x * 2;
const add = (a, b) => a + b;

// ❌ Bad
const double = x => x * 2;
```

### JSX Quotes: Double

```tsx
// ✅ Good
<Button variant="default" size="lg">Click</Button>

// ❌ Bad
<Button variant='default' size='lg'>Click</Button>
```

### Indentation: 2 Spaces

```tsx
// ✅ Good (2 spaces)
function Component() {
  return (
    <div>
      <span>Content</span>
    </div>
  );
}

// ❌ Bad (tabs or 4 spaces)
function Component() {
    return (
        <div>
            <span>Content</span>
        </div>
    );
}
```

## Import Organization

Biome automatically organizes imports. Let it handle sorting.

```tsx
// Biome will organize like this:
import * as React from "react";
import { cva } from "class-variance-authority";

import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";

import { Logo } from "./logo";
```

## Ignored Paths

From `biome.json`, these paths are ignored:

- `node_modules`
- `.next`
- `.vercel`
- `public/r` (generated registry JSON)
- `components/ui` (base shadcn components)

## Linter Rules

- Recommended rules: Enabled
- `useSortedClasses`: Warn (Tailwind class sorting)

## Commands

```bash
# Check for issues
pnpm lint

# Check and auto-fix
pnpm check

# Format files
pnpm biome format --write .
```

## VS Code Integration

If using Biome VS Code extension, it formats on save. Don't also configure Prettier.
